====Obstruents====
*{{IPA|/p, b/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/f, v/}} are [[Labiodental consonant|labiodental]].{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=239}}
*{{IPA|/ʒ/}} is restricted to word-initial position, and occurs only in loanwords from French. It tends to either devoice to {{IPAblink|ʃ}} or be affricated to {{IPAblink|d͡ʒ}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
*{{IPA|/k, kʲ/}} are [[Velar consonant|velar]].{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=239}}
*The exact place of articulation of {{IPA|/x, ɣ/}} varies:
**[[Velar consonant|Velar]] {{IPA|[{{IPA link|x}}, {{IPA link|ɣ}}]}} before and after back vowels and, in the case of {{IPA|/x/}}, also when it is preceded by a back vowel in an intervocalic position between stressed and unstressed syllable.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
**[[Palatal consonant|Palatal]] {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ç}}, {{IPA link|ʝ}}]}} before and after front vowels and, in the case of {{IPA|/x/}}, also after {{IPA|/ə/}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
*Word-initial {{IPA|/x/}} is restricted to the sequence {{IPA|/sx/}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
*{{IPA|/h/}} may be [[H-dropping|dropped]] by some speakers.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
*{{IPA|/p, t, tʲ, k, kʲ, v, z/}} may be affricated to {{IPA|[{{IPA link|p͡ɸ}}, {{IPA link|t͡s}}, t͡sʲ, {{IPA link|k͡x}}, k͡xʲ, {{IPA link|b͡v}}, {{IPA link|d͡z}}]}}. {{Harvcoltxt|Peters|2010}} does not specify the environment(s) in which the affrication of {{IPA|/v/}} and {{IPA|/z/}} takes place. In the case of stops, it occurs in pre-pausal position.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
*{{IPA|/v, z/}} are realized as voiceless {{IPA|[v̥, z̥]}} when they occur between vowels, and often also in word-initial position (in which the devoicing may be only partial). {{IPA|/ɣ/}} is devoiced in a similar manner.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}

====Sonorants====
*{{IPA|/m, β/}} are bilabial.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=239}}
*{{IPA|/n, l, r/}} are alveolar.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=239}}
**{{IPA|/n/}} before {{IPA|/k/}} is pronounced as follows:
***{{IPAblink|n}}, if {{IPA|/k/}} belongs to another morpheme ({{IPA|[nʲ]}} before allomorphemic {{IPA|/kj/}});{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
***{{IPAblink|ŋ}}, if {{IPA|/k/}} belongs to the same morpheme.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
**Word-final {{IPA|[nʲ]}} appears only in loanwords from French.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
**{{IPA|/l/}} tends to be [[Velarization|velarized]], especially postvocalically.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
**{{IPA|/r/}} has a few possible realizations:
***Apical trill {{IPAblink|r}} or an apical fricative {{IPAblink|ɹ̝}} before a stressed vowel in word-initial syllables.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
***Intervocalically and in the onset after a consonant, it may be a tap {{IPAblink|ɾ}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
***Word-final {{IPA|/r/}} is highly variable; the most frequent variants are an apical trill fricative {{IPAblink|r̝}}, an apical fricative {{IPAblink|ɹ̝}} and an apical rhotic affricate {{IPA|[ɾ͡ɹ̝]}}. The last two variants tend to be voiceless ({{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɹ̝̊}}, {{IPA|ɾ̥͡θ̠}}]}}) in pre-pausal position.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}
***The sequence {{IPA|/ər/}} can be vocalized to {{IPAblink|ɐ}} or {{IPAblink|ə}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=245}}
*{{IPA|/ŋ/}} is velar, whereas {{IPA|/j/}} is palatal.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=239}}
*{{IPA|/β, j/}} appear only word-initially and intervocalically.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}

====Final devoicing and assimilation====
Just like Standard Dutch, Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect [[Final-obstruent devoicing|devoices]] all [[obstruent]]s at the ends of words.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}

Morpheme-final {{IPA|/p, t, k/}} may be voiced if a voiced plosive or a vowel follows.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=240}}

===Vowels===
[[File:Orsmaal-Gussenhoven Dutch monophthongs chart.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|[[Monophthong]]s of the Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect, from {{Harvcoltxt|Peters|2010|p=241}}. {{IPA|/ɔː/}} is not shown.]]
[[File:Orsmaal-Gussenhoven Dutch non-centering diphthongs chart - part 1.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Part 1 of non-centering [[diphthong]]s of the Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect, from {{Harvcoltxt|Peters|2010|p=241}}]]
[[File:Orsmaal-Gussenhoven Dutch non-centering diphthongs chart - part 2.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Part 2 of non-centering diphthongs of the Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect, from {{Harvcoltxt|Peters|2010|p=241}}]]
[[File:Orsmaal-Gussenhoven Dutch centering diphthongs chart.svg|thumb|upright=1.13|Centering diphthongs of the Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect, from {{Harvcoltxt|Peters|2010|p=241}}]]

The Orsmaal-Gussenhoven dialect contains 18 monophthong and 12 diphthong phonemes. A notable feature of it are quite unusual contrasts between {{IPA|/eː, øː/}}, {{IPA|/ei, øy/}} and {{IPA|/ɛɪ, œʏ/}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|pp=240–241}}

