* The majority of the vowels ({{IPA|/iː, y, yː, uː, eː, øː, ə, o, oː, ɛː, œː/}}) are close to the canonical values of the corresponding IPA symbols.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=241}}
** {{IPA|/y/}} and {{IPA|/o/}} occur only in few loanwords from French.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=242}}
* {{IPA|/yː, uː, ɒː/}} before {{IPA|/t, d/}} within the same syllable may be realized as centering diphthongs {{IPA|[yə, uə, ɒə]}}, often with a labial glide before the schwa {{IPA|[ywə, uwə, ɒwə]}}. Alternatively, in place of the schwa an unrounded variant of the first vowel may appear: {{IPA|[yi, uɯ, ɒɑ]}}. In the same environment, {{IPA|/øː/}} can be realized as {{IPA|[øjə]}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=242}}
* {{IPA|/ɪ, ʏ, ʊ/}} are phonetically [[Near-close vowel|near-close]]. {{IPA|/ʏ/}} is close to the canonical value of {{angle bracket|{{IPA|ʏ}}}}, yet {{IPA|/ɪ/}} and {{IPA|/ʊ/}} are more peripheral ({{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɪ̟}}, {{IPA link|ʊ̠}}]}}) than the canonical values of {{angle bracket|{{IPA|ɪ, ʊ}}}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=241}}
* {{IPA|/ɛ, œ/}} are closer ({{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɛ̝}}, {{IPA link|œ̝}}]}}) than the canonical values of {{angle bracket|{{IPA|ɛ, œ}}}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=241}}
* {{IPA|/ɔ, ɒ, ɒː/}} are closer ({{IPA|[{{IPA link|ɔ̝}}, {{IPA link|ɒ|ɒ̝}}, {{IPA link|ɒ|ɒ̝ː}}]}} than the canonical values of {{angle bracket|{{IPA|ɔ, ɒ}}}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=241}}
* {{IPA|/ɔː/}} appears only before {{IPA|/t, d/}} and only as a phonetic centering diphthong {{IPA|[ɔə]}}.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=242}}
* {{IPA|/a, aː/}}, which are phonological back vowels, are central {{IPA|[{{IPA link|ä}}, {{IPA link|äː}}]}} phonetically.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=241}}
* When stressed, short vowels cannot occur in open syllables. Exceptions to this rule are high-frequency words like {{IPA|[βa]}} 'what', and loanwords from French, such as {{IPA|[dəˈpo]}} 'depot'.{{sfnp|Peters|2010|p=242}}

{| class="wikitable" style="margin: auto; text-align: center;"
|+ [[Diphthong]] phonemes{{sfnp|Peters|2010|pp=241–242}}
